{"TopicId":52597,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Altitude required for \u0026quot;Near the Sun\u0026quot;?","CreatedByName":"SirJodelstein","CreatedById":62251,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T12:34:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SirJodelstein","CreatedById":62251,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T12:34:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHi, i am flying a mission to explore the sun in close-up detail. I want to put my Periapsis low enough to get the \u0022Near the sun\u0022 science results from the experiments and sensors. Could anyone tell me how close i need to get for this task? Is there maybe a community-maintained thread that lists the science locations for near/high above for all celestials?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-11-10T13:33:38Z\u0022 title=\u002211/10/2013 01:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 10, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by SirJodelstein\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"95tiger59","CreatedById":92346,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T13:18:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ehmm.. my best guess would be 13\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00E2\u20AC\u00B0080\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00E2\u20AC\u00B0000 m which is the 100X warp frame I\u0027m not entirely sure I\u0027ll check though\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T13:24:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/53567-List-of-places-and-biomes-in-v0-22-%28Kerbal-planetary-geology-and-geography%29\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/53567-List-of-places-and-biomes-in-v0-22-%28Kerbal-planetary-geology-and-geography%29\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMillion kilometres.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SRV Ron","CreatedById":69806,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T13:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ECurrently, the physics don\u0027t work correctly for temperature changes. The science bays respond as you are in deep space at present. As far as how close, about a ridiculous 1,500 meters before your ship goes poof!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/q6DqCF4.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022q6DqCF4.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mlb1m7J.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022mlb1m7J.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SirJodelstein","CreatedById":62251,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T13:34:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ethanks a lot!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceweezle","CreatedById":92331,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-10T15:39:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELol, the Sun looks like a giant cookie, I hope your Kerbals brought some milk \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}